    "This is due to the retrieval nature of Nexis search, where an article with at least a single occurrence of any of the search keywords in either the title or body is retrieved as a positive hit.",
    "To sift out the irrelevant articles from the corpus, we utilized the subjects present in the metadata.",
    "Each subject listed in the metadata along with the percentage it is being discussed in the body is part of the Nexis topic taxonomy.",
    "We developed a metadata-based retrieval algorithm that starts with seed-relevant subjects and iteratively chooses relevant documents and relevant subjects until no new relevant subjects are found.",
    "The retrieval algorithm is controlled by the following three parameters."
